<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="11">
The additional character given by Springer and Randall (1999:42) to distinguish 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:30DACC81-A4DA-4A34-9DD5-84730B6BE13A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Blenniidae" genus="Ecsenius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Ecsenius portenoyi Springer 1988:65" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="portenoyi">E. portenoyi</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0340B63F-F5DB-47EE-85F9-E84B81E7A75A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Blenniidae" genus="Ecsenius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Ecsenius pardus Springer 1988:63" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pardus">E. pardus McKinney &amp; Springer</taxonomicName>
is erroneous. It should read, “The interspace between the first and second or second and third spots in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0340B63F-F5DB-47EE-85F9-E84B81E7A75A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Blenniidae" genus="Ecsenius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Ecsenius pardus Springer 1988:63" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pardus">E. pardus</taxonomicName>
is equal to or more than1.5 X the diameter of one of the spots, whereas in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:30DACC81-A4DA-4A34-9DD5-84730B6BE13A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Blenniidae" genus="Ecsenius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Ecsenius portenoyi Springer 1988:65" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="portenoyi">E. portenoyi</taxonomicName>
it is almost always less than the diameter of any of the three spots.”
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
